### 3.3.3. Freeing Memory

To free memory, we use the `free()` function. The `free()` function takes a pointer to the memory we want to free as an argument.

```c
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

typedef struct {
    char name[100];
    int status;
} person;

int main(int argc, char *argv[]) {
    // allocate a new person
    person *p = (person *)malloc(sizeof(person));
